goals.rationale: This visualization will show if there is any seasonal pattern in the CO2 concentration and if the adjusted_CO2 values capture this variation.

goals.question: What is the average CO2 concentration per year?

goals.rationale: This visualization will show the average CO2 concentration per year and help identify any significant changes over time.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='ignore')
    plt.plot(data['Date'], data['CO2'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the trend of CO2 concentration over time?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['CO2'], bins=20, edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('CO2 Concentration')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of CO2 concentration?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    data['Year'] = data['Date'].dt.year
    yearly_avg = data.groupby('Year')['CO2'].mean()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    yearly_avg.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the average CO2 concentration per year?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
